1
00:00:00,767 --> 00:00:04,133
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:00:07,633 --> 00:00:10,700
Thea, Ashley and Jasmine
are a match!

3
00:00:10,833 --> 00:00:11,900
Marj, I am sorry.

4
00:00:12,033 --> 00:00:13,433
We did not agree to the test.

5
00:00:13,567 --> 00:00:15,100
Edward, they already got tested.

6
00:00:15,233 --> 00:00:16,267
What kind of mother are you?

7
00:00:16,400 --> 00:00:18,400
You had her tested without even
telling me?

8
00:00:18,533 --> 00:00:20,100
Because you would not agree.

9
00:00:20,233 --> 00:00:22,133
Besides, Ashley
wanted this too.

10
00:00:22,267 --> 00:00:24,833
Are you not tired of people
getting hurt because of you?

11
00:00:24,967 --> 00:00:26,333
- It is all your fault!
- [SLAPS]

12
00:00:26,467 --> 00:00:28,133
People only change their minds

13
00:00:28,267 --> 00:00:30,967
when they are forced to face
what they avoid.

14
00:00:31,100 --> 00:00:32,833
When will the operation be

15
00:00:32,967 --> 00:00:35,167
so our family trip
can finally happen?

16
00:00:35,333 --> 00:00:36,400
Soon, my child.

17
00:00:36,533 --> 00:00:38,967
They are just finalizing
the procedure.

18
00:00:39,100 --> 00:00:42,133
What if there is really
something they need to face?

19
00:00:42,267 --> 00:00:43,367
Go on, my grandchild.

20
00:00:43,500 --> 00:00:45,700
I am listening. He will be
Marj's lawyer

21
00:00:45,833 --> 00:00:49,133
if she files a case against you
for what you did to Jobert.

22
00:00:49,267 --> 00:00:50,567
Let us settle this.

23
00:00:50,700 --> 00:00:53,167
Fine, what are we settling?

24
00:00:53,300 --> 00:00:55,267
Allow Ashley to donate
to Jasmine.

25
00:00:55,400 --> 00:00:56,833
- Unbelievable!
- One hundred fifty

26
00:00:56,967 --> 00:00:57,900
million pesos.

27
00:00:58,033 --> 00:00:59,500
What?

28
00:00:59,633 --> 00:01:03,733
One hundred fifty million pesos?

29
00:01:49,033 --> 00:01:50,567
Did you hear that, my child?

30
00:01:50,700 --> 00:01:52,867
You have a donor now,
you and Ashley are a match!

31
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:54,800
So there really is a chance?

32
00:01:54,933 --> 00:01:56,433
Not just a chance,

33
00:01:56,567 --> 00:01:58,100
you will get better.

34
00:01:59,533 --> 00:02:00,533
But

35
00:02:01,833 --> 00:02:06,267
test consent is different from
the actual extraction.

36
00:02:06,400 --> 00:02:08,700
What about Ashley then?

37
00:02:08,833 --> 00:02:10,633
What if she suddenly backs out

38
00:02:10,767 --> 00:02:12,767
or Aunt and Uncle refuse?

39
00:02:12,900 --> 00:02:14,833
No, no, that will not happen,
my child.

40
00:02:15,900 --> 00:02:17,333
We are almost there.

41
00:02:17,467 --> 00:02:20,333
We will set your procedure soon.

42
00:02:20,467 --> 00:02:21,867
I do not know, Mom.

43
00:02:23,233 --> 00:02:24,600
Sometimes I feel

44
00:02:24,733 --> 00:02:27,267
my life is full of almosts.

45
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:28,733
Almost healed,

46
00:02:28,867 --> 00:02:30,700
almost normal,

47
00:02:30,833 --> 00:02:33,167
almost okay as a family.

48
00:02:34,300 --> 00:02:37,333
It is tiring to hope
when nothing is certain.

49
00:02:37,467 --> 00:02:40,867
My child, do not think that way.

50
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,367
Think instead that
once you get better,

51
00:02:43,500 --> 00:02:44,867
we will leave this place.

52
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:46,433
You will go home.

53
00:02:46,567 --> 00:02:48,533
Do you want to go to the beach?

54
00:02:48,700 --> 00:02:51,100
Anywhere, wherever you want.

55
00:02:51,233 --> 00:02:52,900
Nature trekking?

56
00:02:53,033 --> 00:02:54,667
Stargazing?

57
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:56,267
Road trip?

58
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:58,433
Anything you want.

59
00:02:59,467 --> 00:03:01,300
Can I drive already?

60
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:04,167
Jasmine,

61
00:03:04,300 --> 00:03:06,233
you really are something,
of course!

62
00:03:06,367 --> 00:03:08,400
Just take driving lessons

63
00:03:08,533 --> 00:03:12,567
and get a student permit. It's
not that easy.

64
00:03:12,700 --> 00:03:14,700
I will teach you how to drive.

65
00:03:14,833 --> 00:03:17,033
Manual transmission, for real.

66
00:03:17,167 --> 00:03:19,900
Will you come with us on
the stargazing trip, Dad?

67
00:03:27,600 --> 00:03:29,133
Yes.

68
00:03:29,267 --> 00:03:30,800
The three of us together.

69
00:03:34,967 --> 00:03:36,900
We will bring a tent

70
00:03:37,033 --> 00:03:39,167
and all your favorite snacks.

71
00:03:40,600 --> 00:03:43,167
We will go somewhere
with little light

72
00:03:43,300 --> 00:03:46,367
so we can see the stars.

73
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:48,033
No phones,

74
00:03:48,167 --> 00:03:50,700
no hospital, no problems.

75
00:03:50,833 --> 00:03:54,433
Then we will wait
for a shooting star.

76
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:55,900
We will make a wish.

77
00:03:56,033 --> 00:03:58,400
No need to wish

78
00:03:58,533 --> 00:04:01,800
because we are together
and happy.

79
00:04:01,933 --> 00:04:04,600
Best wish granted ever.

80
00:04:07,633 --> 00:04:14,233
[DRAMATIC]

81
00:04:14,367 --> 00:04:19,700
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

82
00:04:32,767 --> 00:04:34,467
How long are you
checked in here?

83
00:04:35,633 --> 00:04:36,533
I do not know.

84
00:04:36,667 --> 00:04:38,233
I am still looking for a place.

85
00:04:39,467 --> 00:04:42,733
[PHONE RINGING]

86
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:53,200
[UNSETTLING]

87
00:04:55,933 --> 00:04:57,700
Are they still pressuring you
about the test?

88
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:01,033
Maybe

89
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:03,733
you are still giving them hope
and accommodating them.

90
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:12,000
Edward,

91
00:05:12,133 --> 00:05:15,000
can you endure Jasmine's
condition getting worse?

92
00:05:16,033 --> 00:05:17,267
If Ashley were the one who
was sick,

93
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:19,867
I feel Paolo would not hesitate.

94
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:20,900
Because what?

95
00:05:24,100 --> 00:05:26,067
Even Marj

96
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:30,333
would help Ashley if she
were in Jasmine's situation.

97
00:05:30,467 --> 00:05:31,433
Dad,

98
00:05:32,833 --> 00:05:35,400
are you not worried
about Jasmine?

99
00:05:38,733 --> 00:05:40,300
[SIGHS]

100
00:05:40,433 --> 00:05:42,433
My heart aches for Jasmine.

101
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:46,867
I can't watch what is happening
to her, but, my child.

102
00:05:48,767 --> 00:05:50,333
But you are my responsibility.

103
00:05:51,400 --> 00:05:53,133
You are my priority.

104
00:05:56,333 --> 00:05:58,367
So we will just let it be?

105
00:05:58,500 --> 00:05:59,667
Thea,

106
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:01,733
one mistake
in the operating room,

107
00:06:01,867 --> 00:06:04,967
one mistake, one complication,

108
00:06:05,100 --> 00:06:07,967
we will carry that for life.

109
00:06:09,167 --> 00:06:10,933
Do you want Ashley to be harmed?

110
00:06:12,167 --> 00:06:13,733
Can you live

111
00:06:13,867 --> 00:06:15,333
knowing you decided that?

112
00:06:28,367 --> 00:06:29,967
<i>If they do not match,
life goes on.</i>

113
00:06:30,100 --> 00:06:31,033
<i> But if they match,</i>

114
00:06:31,167 --> 00:06:32,700
<i> she will donate to Jasmine.</i>

115
00:06:34,233 --> 00:06:36,200
This is the last time
I am going to say this .

116
00:06:37,233 --> 00:06:39,400
Ashley's body is off limits.

117
00:06:40,500 --> 00:06:45,000
They cannot touch Ashley
as if they have a right to her .

118
00:06:45,133 --> 00:06:46,100
Dad!

119
00:06:46,233 --> 00:06:51,100
[INTENSE]

120
00:07:05,233 --> 00:07:06,233
Thea!

121
00:07:07,267 --> 00:07:09,100
Are you avoiding us?

122
00:07:09,233 --> 00:07:11,533
Did you not receive my text?

123
00:07:11,667 --> 00:07:14,633
Ashley and Jasmine are matched.

124
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:16,267
[SIGHS]

125
00:07:16,400 --> 00:07:18,967
I received your messages.

126
00:07:19,100 --> 00:07:20,867
But Edward refuses.

127
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,333
I will talk to him again.

128
00:07:22,467 --> 00:07:23,800
I am just waiting
for the right time.

129
00:07:23,933 --> 00:07:26,600
Thea, I do not have tomorrow!
I do not have right time.

130
00:07:26,733 --> 00:07:30,867
I do not even know if my child
has a tomorrow.

131
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:32,567
Why are you so demanding?

132
00:07:32,700 --> 00:07:35,267
You are the one asking
for a favor.

133
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:38,800
Marj, my child
is also involved here.

134
00:07:38,933 --> 00:07:42,000
Do you think I want to talk
to you?

135
00:07:42,133 --> 00:07:45,567
It is against my will to beg
someone like you,

136
00:07:45,700 --> 00:07:47,567
but I choose to be a mother

137
00:07:47,700 --> 00:07:50,567
rather than a betrayed spouse.

138
00:07:50,733 --> 00:07:53,833
Thea, if I need to beg Edward.

139
00:07:54,867 --> 00:07:56,667
Not now, it is chaotic.

140
00:07:58,867 --> 00:07:59,933
Marj.

141
00:08:01,233 --> 00:08:02,367
Edward.

142
00:08:04,700 --> 00:08:05,767
Marj, I am sorry.

143
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:08,667
We do not agree to the test.

144
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:10,867
I already told Paolo that.

145
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:13,267
Edward, they already got tested.

146
00:08:13,400 --> 00:08:16,700
[INTENSE]

147
00:08:16,833 --> 00:08:17,633
What?

148
00:08:21,833 --> 00:08:23,467
You got tested behind my back?

149
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:29,267
Edward, Ashley and Jasmine
are matched.

150
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:30,900
I am begging you.

151
00:08:31,033 --> 00:08:33,833
The doctor needs a schedule
for the transplant

152
00:08:33,967 --> 00:08:35,633
as soon as possible.

153
00:08:36,667 --> 00:08:39,633
Please, allow Ashley
to help Jasmine.

154
00:08:39,767 --> 00:08:44,367
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

155
00:08:50,567 --> 00:08:51,667
Go upstairs now.

156
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:54,133
- I will take you, lets go.
- Edward, please, please.

157
00:08:54,300 --> 00:08:55,467
No more.

158
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:57,533
I am not agreeing.

159
00:08:57,667 --> 00:08:59,500
Edward, my child's life
is at stake.

160
00:08:59,633 --> 00:09:01,167
And my child's life
is also at stake.

161
00:09:02,700 --> 00:09:04,767
If I have to be seen as cruel
in everyone's eyes,

162
00:09:04,900 --> 00:09:05,867
I will do it!

163
00:09:07,067 --> 00:09:09,267
As long as I do not allow
my child to be used

164
00:09:09,400 --> 00:09:10,833
especially without my consent!

165
00:09:12,100 --> 00:09:13,633
Marj,

166
00:09:13,767 --> 00:09:16,833
They silenced me for so long
in this family, but this time,

167
00:09:16,967 --> 00:09:18,367
I will decide.

168
00:09:18,500 --> 00:09:19,700
I will not allow it.

169
00:09:19,833 --> 00:09:21,667
- I am begging you.
- Ashley,

170
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:23,400
- let's go.
- Please, I am begging you.

171
00:09:23,533 --> 00:09:25,333
Let Ashley help.

172
00:09:25,467 --> 00:09:27,300
Marj, it is not allowed!

173
00:09:27,433 --> 00:09:28,867
We cannot help you, I am sorry.

174
00:09:29,033 --> 00:09:29,967
Please leave.

175
00:09:32,033 --> 00:09:34,000
I thought you were different.

176
00:09:34,133 --> 00:09:36,867
I thought you had a heart.

177
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:39,367
But you are selfish too.

178
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:44,533
[INTENSE]

179
00:09:57,467 --> 00:09:59,200
What kind of mother are you?

180
00:09:59,333 --> 00:10:01,867
You had her tested
without even telling me?

181
00:10:02,033 --> 00:10:03,500
You would not agree anyway.

182
00:10:03,633 --> 00:10:05,600
Besides, Ashley wanted it too.

183
00:10:05,733 --> 00:10:07,033
And Jasmine deserves
compassion too.

184
00:10:07,167 --> 00:10:08,967
Hey, why is that?

185
00:10:09,100 --> 00:10:13,067
Are you still hoping to return
to my family if you help?

186
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:16,367
Edward, not everything
is about you.

187
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:18,567
I am also Ashley's parent!

188
00:10:18,700 --> 00:10:19,567
I did not force her.

189
00:10:19,700 --> 00:10:20,967
I did not use her.

190
00:10:21,100 --> 00:10:22,700
I listened to our child.

191
00:10:22,833 --> 00:10:24,833
I do not believe your reasoning.

192
00:10:24,967 --> 00:10:27,833
You would not do that without
gaining something.

193
00:10:27,967 --> 00:10:29,933
Why do you still refuse?

194
00:10:30,067 --> 00:10:32,600
I already matched, right?

195
00:10:32,733 --> 00:10:36,100
What about Jasmine? What if
something happens to Jasmine?

196
00:10:36,267 --> 00:10:37,967
If I have a chance
and do nothing,

197
00:10:38,100 --> 00:10:39,367
I would not be able to live
with that.

198
00:10:39,500 --> 00:10:40,867
My child,

199
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,433
that is not just a simple test.

200
00:10:43,567 --> 00:10:44,933
There is a process

201
00:10:45,067 --> 00:10:46,467
and there are risks.

202
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:47,567
And as your parent,

203
00:10:47,700 --> 00:10:49,167
it is my responsibility

204
00:10:49,300 --> 00:10:51,833
to not let you be harmed
by anyone.

205
00:10:51,967 --> 00:10:53,233
Dad, I can survive this.

206
00:10:53,367 --> 00:10:55,467
Knowing I did
something meaningful.

207
00:10:55,600 --> 00:10:59,300
My child, I could not bear it if
something bad happened to you.

208
00:11:00,767 --> 00:11:02,833
So we are just going to let
Jas be?

209
00:11:02,967 --> 00:11:04,333
We are just going
to let her die?

210
00:11:04,467 --> 00:11:05,533
[SIGHS]

211
00:11:05,667 --> 00:11:07,433
No.

212
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:10,133
They will find another way
if needed.

213
00:11:10,267 --> 00:11:12,233
What if I am really the way?

214
00:11:14,800 --> 00:11:15,767
Mom,

215
00:11:17,133 --> 00:11:18,567
after everything,

216
00:11:19,800 --> 00:11:23,133
is this not the least we can do?

217
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:26,233
Ashley...

218
00:11:26,367 --> 00:11:27,933
Are you not getting tired.

219
00:11:31,233 --> 00:11:34,100
Are you not tired of people
getting hurt because of you?

220
00:11:37,133 --> 00:11:38,600
Ashley, do not talk like that.

221
00:11:38,733 --> 00:11:40,567
Why not?

222
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:42,433
It is true.

223
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:44,133
If not because of you,

224
00:11:44,267 --> 00:11:46,333
everything would not be
in chaos.

225
00:11:46,467 --> 00:11:47,900
This is all your fault!

226
00:11:49,267 --> 00:11:51,400
The cheating, everything,

227
00:11:51,533 --> 00:11:53,700
even what happened
to Uncle Jobert!

228
00:11:53,833 --> 00:11:55,533
- [SLAPS]
- Enough!

229
00:11:55,667 --> 00:11:56,833
Thea!

230
00:11:56,967 --> 00:12:00,333
[INTENSE]

231
00:12:00,467 --> 00:12:02,667
- [SOBBING]
- My child, I am sorry.

232
00:12:04,133 --> 00:12:06,400
My child, I am sorry.

233
00:12:06,533 --> 00:12:07,767
I understand now.

234
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:13,867
Maybe I really was a mistake.

235
00:12:15,433 --> 00:12:18,267
If I had not existed
from your lies,

236
00:12:19,333 --> 00:12:21,067
you would not be like this.

237
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:23,833
[INTENSE]

238
00:12:26,100 --> 00:12:29,633
This is my only chance to do
something right even just once.

239
00:12:31,467 --> 00:12:33,000
To have value.

240
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:37,300
So please,

241
00:12:37,433 --> 00:12:39,467
do not take this away from me.

242
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:46,067
Ashley, my child.

243
00:12:46,200 --> 00:12:47,033
Do not follow me anymore

244
00:12:47,167 --> 00:12:50,067
if you still want me
to come back.

245
00:12:50,233 --> 00:12:55,167
[INTENSE]

246
00:12:58,800 --> 00:13:02,533
I am tired.

247
00:13:05,267 --> 00:13:07,267
Everything is always forbidden.

248
00:13:07,400 --> 00:13:08,767
Not allowed.

249
00:13:10,533 --> 00:13:12,100
You are still young.

250
00:13:12,233 --> 00:13:14,100
Others will decide for you.

251
00:13:15,933 --> 00:13:17,567
This is my body.

252
00:13:17,700 --> 00:13:19,033
My rules.

253
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:24,533
When can I decide for myself?

254
00:13:24,700 --> 00:13:27,200
Without anyone getting angry
at me?

255
00:13:27,333 --> 00:13:29,367
Without hurting anyone?

256
00:13:30,567 --> 00:13:33,367
It feels like everyone
has a say over my body.

257
00:13:34,867 --> 00:13:36,233
In my life.

258
00:13:38,500 --> 00:13:40,367
If I help,

259
00:13:40,500 --> 00:13:41,567
it is drama.

260
00:13:41,700 --> 00:13:43,133
If I do not help,

261
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:46,400
I am selfish.

262
00:13:46,533 --> 00:13:47,400
That is how they see me!

263
00:13:47,533 --> 00:13:49,100
I am selfish!

264
00:13:51,500 --> 00:13:53,200
Do you want to help, Ash?

265
00:13:53,333 --> 00:13:55,933
[DRAMATIC]

266
00:13:59,433 --> 00:14:01,033
But it is unfair.

267
00:14:02,633 --> 00:14:04,833
When I choose,

268
00:14:04,967 --> 00:14:06,900
someone still gets hurt.

269
00:14:07,967 --> 00:14:09,800
You choose to love.

270
00:14:09,933 --> 00:14:11,833
You choose to care.

271
00:14:11,967 --> 00:14:13,667
That is why I like you, Ashley.

272
00:14:17,333 --> 00:14:20,567
I just do not want
to see you suffer.

273
00:14:20,700 --> 00:14:21,867
Xander,

274
00:14:25,500 --> 00:14:26,633
thank you.

275
00:14:29,733 --> 00:14:31,667
Thank you for being here
with me.

276
00:14:33,800 --> 00:14:35,533
You know,

277
00:14:35,667 --> 00:14:37,633
you are the only one I know

278
00:14:37,767 --> 00:14:39,767
who does not see me only
as a donor.

279
00:14:41,033 --> 00:14:43,367
Or a child who needs protection.

280
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:47,867
That I am not a problem.

281
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:49,333
Thank you.

282
00:14:49,467 --> 00:14:50,833
Thank you, Ashley.

283
00:14:50,967 --> 00:14:55,767
[DRAMATIC]

284
00:15:05,767 --> 00:15:10,133
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

285
00:15:19,633 --> 00:15:21,533
This is just a teaser.

286
00:15:21,667 --> 00:15:24,033
So when you are discharged,

287
00:15:24,167 --> 00:15:25,533
you will not be surprised.

288
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:31,300
This feels like stargazing
on an outer space level, Dad.

289
00:15:31,433 --> 00:15:33,467
Your dad is really amazing.

290
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:34,600
Mom.

291
00:15:36,400 --> 00:15:39,267
[DRAMATIC]

292
00:15:39,400 --> 00:15:44,367
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

293
00:16:01,800 --> 00:16:03,633
When will the operation be

294
00:16:03,767 --> 00:16:08,633
so our family trip outside
this hospital can happen?

295
00:16:08,800 --> 00:16:10,967
Are you excited?

296
00:16:11,100 --> 00:16:12,967
Soon, my child.

297
00:16:13,100 --> 00:16:15,500
They are just finalizing
the procedure.

298
00:16:15,633 --> 00:16:19,867
[DRAMATIC]

299
00:16:27,433 --> 00:16:31,833
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

300
00:17:03,100 --> 00:17:04,333
Dear, breathe.

301
00:17:04,467 --> 00:17:06,000
Breathe.

302
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:12,100
[DRAMATIC]

303
00:17:14,300 --> 00:17:16,633
I really just wanted to help,

304
00:17:16,800 --> 00:17:18,967
Grandmother.

305
00:17:19,100 --> 00:17:20,967
I truly just wanted to help.

306
00:17:22,133 --> 00:17:25,467
But it feels like Dad
is not listening to me.

307
00:17:27,133 --> 00:17:29,067
- [SIGHS]
- But you know,

308
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:31,967
your grandfaher and I
are on your side.

309
00:17:32,100 --> 00:17:34,400
We understand you.

310
00:17:34,533 --> 00:17:36,833
And you are so brave
and generous

311
00:17:36,967 --> 00:17:39,300
for offering your help
to Jasmine.

312
00:17:40,867 --> 00:17:42,667
I tried

313
00:17:42,800 --> 00:17:44,800
to convince your mother,

314
00:17:44,933 --> 00:17:46,767
I even offered help.

315
00:17:48,267 --> 00:17:50,167
But

316
00:17:50,300 --> 00:17:52,100
what do you think
your father did

317
00:17:52,233 --> 00:17:53,900
to make Thea so stubborn?

318
00:17:54,033 --> 00:17:57,267
Greg, not in front of our
grandchild, please.

319
00:17:58,733 --> 00:18:00,733
Honestly, Ashley,

320
00:18:00,867 --> 00:18:03,633
your mother makes decisions
when she is cornered.

321
00:18:06,100 --> 00:18:08,367
When there is something

322
00:18:08,500 --> 00:18:10,267
to protect,

323
00:18:10,400 --> 00:18:12,100
when there is something to hide.

324
00:18:12,233 --> 00:18:13,333
Greg!

325
00:18:14,367 --> 00:18:15,967
What I am saying is,

326
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:20,000
people only change their minds

327
00:18:20,133 --> 00:18:22,667
when they are forced to face

328
00:18:22,833 --> 00:18:24,300
what they avoid.

329
00:18:25,433 --> 00:18:26,667
But

330
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:28,567
it is not your obligation

331
00:18:28,700 --> 00:18:30,467
to do that to your parents

332
00:18:30,600 --> 00:18:32,700
just to get what you want,
Ashley.

333
00:18:34,800 --> 00:18:36,167
You are still young.

334
00:18:38,333 --> 00:18:40,200
I am not a child anymore.

335
00:18:44,600 --> 00:18:45,967
What if

336
00:18:47,867 --> 00:18:50,333
there really is something they
need to face?

337
00:18:54,367 --> 00:18:55,467
Go on, my grandchild.

338
00:18:55,633 --> 00:18:56,633
I am listening.

339
00:18:56,767 --> 00:18:58,733
[TENSE]

340
00:19:02,900 --> 00:19:05,000
I do not want to say this to
ruin her reputation

341
00:19:05,133 --> 00:19:06,633
or anything like that.

342
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:10,333
I also do not want
to embarrass her.

343
00:19:11,367 --> 00:19:13,733
But if Jasmine's life
is at stake,

344
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:17,967
I can no longer stay silent.

345
00:19:19,433 --> 00:19:21,233
Ashley, what are you saying?

346
00:19:24,833 --> 00:19:27,633
If there is a way to correct
my mother's mistakes

347
00:19:27,767 --> 00:19:29,333
even little by little.

348
00:19:30,367 --> 00:19:34,433
If I need to tell the truth
to save Jasmine,

349
00:19:35,667 --> 00:19:37,700
I will do it.

350
00:19:37,833 --> 00:19:44,567
[INTENSE]

351
00:19:55,533 --> 00:19:57,300
Don't worry too much.

352
00:19:57,433 --> 00:19:59,867
Ashley might just be
cooling off.

353
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,967
I am sure she will
come home later.

354
00:20:04,867 --> 00:20:06,967
I hope Ashley understands
that we are being strict

355
00:20:07,100 --> 00:20:09,233
because we want to protect her,

356
00:20:09,367 --> 00:20:10,700
so she does not get hurt.

357
00:20:11,733 --> 00:20:13,000
[PHONE BEEP]

358
00:20:15,767 --> 00:20:18,100
[INTENSE]

359
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:21,200
Dad texted.

360
00:20:22,367 --> 00:20:24,367
Ashley is there, apparently.

361
00:20:24,500 --> 00:20:26,100
He wants us to go there.

362
00:20:26,233 --> 00:20:27,500
Why did she go there?

363
00:20:29,333 --> 00:20:30,633
I do not know.

364
00:20:30,767 --> 00:20:33,500
- Let us just pick her up.
- Wait, for him to text us?

365
00:20:33,633 --> 00:20:36,500
He would not just text
about where his grandchild is.

366
00:20:37,633 --> 00:20:38,967
He has something planned.

367
00:20:39,100 --> 00:20:40,500
He is going to interfere again.

368
00:20:40,633 --> 00:20:43,967
[INTENSE]

369
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:49,867
[DOORBELL RINGS]

370
00:21:01,067 --> 00:21:02,933
Thank you for coming.

371
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:09,667
We are just going to pick up
Ashley.

372
00:21:09,833 --> 00:21:12,100
Why does this feel like
a family meeting?

373
00:21:12,233 --> 00:21:13,500
And who is he?

374
00:21:13,633 --> 00:21:15,033
[CHUCKLES]

375
00:21:15,167 --> 00:21:17,600
Aren't you familiar
with Attorney Mamucod?

376
00:21:18,633 --> 00:21:22,167
Part of Torrecampo Realty's
legal team.

377
00:21:22,300 --> 00:21:24,300
He will be Marj's lawyer

378
00:21:24,433 --> 00:21:26,733
if she files a case against you

379
00:21:26,867 --> 00:21:28,933
for what you did to Jobert.

380
00:21:29,067 --> 00:21:30,633
[INTENSE]

381
00:21:30,767 --> 00:21:32,033
Ashley.

382
00:21:34,267 --> 00:21:37,600
- Whatever Ashley said...
- Stop it!

383
00:21:37,733 --> 00:21:39,267
[SIGHS]

384
00:21:39,400 --> 00:21:42,200
So, you just called us here
to threaten us?

385
00:21:44,300 --> 00:21:45,833
- Come here!
- Sit!

386
00:21:46,933 --> 00:21:47,967
Sit down!

387
00:21:48,100 --> 00:21:51,900
[INTENSE]

388
00:21:55,633 --> 00:21:57,300
Personally,

389
00:21:57,433 --> 00:21:58,967
I do not want this
to reach court.

390
00:22:00,267 --> 00:22:02,167
Bad publicity.

391
00:22:02,300 --> 00:22:04,367
That is why it is better

392
00:22:04,500 --> 00:22:05,867
to settle this.

393
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:08,467
Fine, what kind of settlement
is that?

394
00:22:08,600 --> 00:22:10,433
It's where only your favorite
child benefits.

395
00:22:10,567 --> 00:22:13,300
Edward, you know that
is not true.

396
00:22:15,433 --> 00:22:17,333
Allow Ashley to donate
to Jasmine.

397
00:22:17,467 --> 00:22:19,300
[HUFFS]

398
00:22:19,433 --> 00:22:21,567
In exchange for not filing
a case against me?

399
00:22:21,700 --> 00:22:24,167
My job, my support for Ashley?

400
00:22:24,300 --> 00:22:25,700
What else?

401
00:22:25,833 --> 00:22:27,400
- Unbelievable!
- One hundred fifty

402
00:22:27,533 --> 00:22:29,300
million pesos.

403
00:22:29,433 --> 00:22:30,867
What?

404
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:35,100
One hundred fifty million pesos?

405
00:22:35,233 --> 00:22:40,267
[INTENSE]

406
00:22:45,500 --> 00:22:46,733
Cash settlement.

407
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:50,200
No case, no hearing,

408
00:22:50,333 --> 00:22:53,767
no scandal, and you walk away
with security.

409
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:57,000
Thanks again
to your loving mother.

410
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:00,567
Edward,

411
00:23:00,700 --> 00:23:03,633
we will make sure
that Ashley is protected.

412
00:23:05,267 --> 00:23:07,433
We will not put her in danger.

413
00:23:10,667 --> 00:23:11,633
So

414
00:23:12,700 --> 00:23:15,700
you are paying us
to give you my child?

415
00:23:17,767 --> 00:23:19,567
We are not desperate!

416
00:23:19,700 --> 00:23:21,167
And I am not stupid!

417
00:23:22,267 --> 00:23:23,300
Do you think I do not know

418
00:23:23,433 --> 00:23:25,933
how much you are paying
for the hotel?

419
00:23:26,067 --> 00:23:30,867
How many credit cards you cycled
just to maintain your image?

420
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:32,700
You have no stable jobs!

421
00:23:33,900 --> 00:23:36,000
All start-ups that do not earn!

422
00:23:36,133 --> 00:23:38,533
All plans that never succeed!

423
00:23:38,667 --> 00:23:40,200
Greg, that is too much!

424
00:23:41,233 --> 00:23:42,867
Edward, my child!

425
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:46,100
Just think of it as a reward

426
00:23:46,233 --> 00:23:48,267
for saving Jasmine's life.

427
00:23:48,400 --> 00:23:51,267
[INTENSE]

428
00:23:55,767 --> 00:23:57,633
A child's life is at stake!

429
00:23:59,633 --> 00:24:00,900
I have made my decision.

430
00:24:05,900 --> 00:24:08,133
I will not trade my child
for money.

431
00:24:09,167 --> 00:24:11,867
And I will not turn my child's
body into a transaction.

432
00:24:13,367 --> 00:24:16,933
[INTENSE]

433
00:24:17,067 --> 00:24:18,400
What kind of person are you?

434
00:24:19,700 --> 00:24:21,300
You had the chance to help.

435
00:24:22,433 --> 00:24:25,000
You had the chance
to save Jasmine.

436
00:24:25,133 --> 00:24:27,233
And you chose
to protect yourselves.

437
00:24:27,367 --> 00:24:29,300
I have no one else left
to protect.

438
00:24:30,867 --> 00:24:32,333
There is nothing left for me!

439
00:24:33,567 --> 00:24:34,633
I lost everything!

440
00:24:34,767 --> 00:24:38,500
The respect I worked hard for,
my family,

441
00:24:38,633 --> 00:24:40,567
my home!

442
00:24:40,700 --> 00:24:42,900
Ashley is my whole world now.

443
00:24:43,033 --> 00:24:45,800
And I will not allow my world
to be traded

444
00:24:45,933 --> 00:24:47,600
just to fix yours!

445
00:24:49,200 --> 00:24:50,833
Enough!

446
00:24:50,967 --> 00:24:52,467
This meeting is over.

447
00:24:55,067 --> 00:24:55,967
Ashley.

448
00:24:59,233 --> 00:25:00,467
Ashley, let's go!

449
00:25:02,500 --> 00:25:08,033
[INTENSE]

450
00:25:08,167 --> 00:25:11,700
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

451
00:25:21,700 --> 00:25:25,033
Why is Attorney Mamucod's
associate here

452
00:25:25,167 --> 00:25:27,233
when there was no legal
settlement?

453
00:25:27,367 --> 00:25:28,700
I just fixed something.

454
00:25:28,833 --> 00:25:30,033
I revised the will.

455
00:25:30,167 --> 00:25:31,233
I removed Edward.

456
00:25:31,367 --> 00:25:32,633
What?

457
00:25:32,767 --> 00:25:35,567
You removed your own child
from your will?

458
00:25:35,733 --> 00:25:38,267
Edward refused to sell
his child!

459
00:25:38,400 --> 00:25:40,000
That is not disrespect.

460
00:25:40,133 --> 00:25:41,733
That is parenting.

461
00:25:41,867 --> 00:25:42,600
That is not my point.

462
00:25:42,733 --> 00:25:44,967
Then what is your point, Greg?

463
00:25:46,500 --> 00:25:47,833
Does Edward know about this?

464
00:25:47,967 --> 00:25:49,667
Edward and I
have different views

465
00:25:49,800 --> 00:25:51,133
on what is best for Ashley.

466
00:25:51,267 --> 00:25:52,233
And as her mother,

467
00:25:52,367 --> 00:25:53,633
I need to make the decision.

468
00:25:53,767 --> 00:25:55,067
Are you sure about this?

469
00:25:55,200 --> 00:25:57,100
Nothing is certain in our lives
right now.

470
00:25:57,233 --> 00:26:00,200
But I can stand by this more
than living with guilt.

471
00:26:00,333 --> 00:26:03,200
Because there is a child
I would be allowing to die.

472
00:26:03,333 --> 00:26:04,767
We can finally leave this mess.

473
00:26:04,900 --> 00:26:06,767
Our lives will be better even if
it is just the two of us.

474
00:26:06,900 --> 00:26:08,833
They will not take you
from me so easily.

475
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:10,867
I am scared, Mom.

476
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:12,000
Ashley.

477
00:26:12,133 --> 00:26:13,200
What you mean is,

478
00:26:13,333 --> 00:26:14,667
when you do not get your way,

479
00:26:14,800 --> 00:26:18,633
you make him feel that he has
no right to be your son!

480
00:26:18,767 --> 00:26:21,733
He really has no right
to be included in my will.

481
00:26:21,867 --> 00:26:23,067
What do you mean?
